<%= SCOPE %> | WRITE_SHEETS
<%= HEADERS %> | <%= HEADER_AUTH %><br/><%= HEADER_CT_JSON %>
<%= REQUEST %> | [Attachment object](#attachment-object) limited to the following attributes:<ul><li>name</li><li>description (applicable when attaching to sheet or row only)</li><li>url</li><li>attachmentType</li><li>attachmentSubType</li></ul>
<%= RETURNS %> | [Result object](#result-object) containing an [Attachment object](#attachment-object) for the newly created attachment

The URL can be any of the following:
<ul>
<li>Normal URL (attachmentType "LINK")</li>
<li>Google Drive URL (attachmentType "GOOGLE_DRIVE")</li>
<li>Box.com URL (attachmentType "BOX_COM")</li>
<li>Dropbox URL (attachmentType "DROPBOX")</li>
<li>Evernote URL (attachmentType "EVERNOTE")</li>
<li>Egnyte URL (attachmentType "EGNYTE")</li>
<li>OneDrive URL (attachmentType "ONEDRIVE")</li>
</ul>

<aside class="notice">For GOOGLE_DRIVE attachments that are Google Docs, the <b>attachmentSubType</b> attribute can be optionally included to indicate the type of a file.  Valid values are: "DOCUMENT", "SPREADSHEET", "PRESENTATION", "PDF", "DRAWING".</aside>

<aside class="notice">For EGNYTE attachments which are Folders, the <b>attachmentSubType</b> attribute must be included with a value of "FOLDER".</aside>

<aside class="notice">When the attachment type is BOX_COM, DROPBOX, ONEDRIVE, EGNYTE (without an <b>attachmentSubType</b> specified), or GOOGLE_DRIVE (without an <b>attachmentSubType</b> specified), the mimeType will be derived by the file extension specified on the <b>name</b> attribute.</aside>
